claim.claim-text:
1. A color image conversion method for reducing the image data size of a monochrome document scanned by a image input device, comprising the steps of:
setting a tolerable error range for pixels;
reading a source document to generate an original color image file;
checking whether the pixel values derived from the original color image file fall within the tolerable error range;
converting the original color image file into a monochrome image file to reduce the data, if all of the pixel values derived from the original color image file fall within the tolerable error range; and
storing the converted file.
